===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A common substance, chemically consisting mainly of [[sodium chloride]] ([[NaCl]]), used extensively as a [[condiment]] and [[preservative]].
# {{chemistry}} One of the [[compound]]s formed from the [[reaction]] of an [[acid]] with a [[base]], where a positive [[ion]] replaces a [[hydrogen]] of the acid.
# A kind of [[marsh]] at the shore of a sea (short for [[salt marsh]], apparently not in a wide-spread use).
# {{slang}} A [[sailor]] (also ''[[old salt]]'').
#* '''1851''', Herman Melville, ''Moby-Dick''
#*: I never go as a passenger; nor, though I am something of a '''salt''', do I ever go to sea as a Commodore, or a Captain, or a Cook.
